        public CsvSchemaCell(String sName)
        Creates a CSV string cell with specified name. The format can be added after creation by using the SchemaCell.setCellFormat(CellType, String) method.
        Parameters:
        sName - The name of the cell.

      • CsvSchemaCell

        public CsvSchemaCell(String sName,
                     CellType type,
                     String pattern,
                     Locale locale)
        Creates a CSV schema cell with the specified name and format parameters.
        Parameters:
        sName - The name of the cell.
        type - The type of the cell.
        pattern - The pattern to use while formatting and parsing. The pattern has different meaning depending on the type of the cell.
        locale - The locale to use while formatting and parsing dates and numbers that are locale specific. If null, US locale is used.

      • getMaxLength

        public int getMaxLength()
        The maximum number of characters that are read or written to/from the cell. Input and output value will be silently truncated to this length. If you want to get an error when field is to long, use the format regexp pattern instead.
        Returns:
        the maxLength

      • setMaxLength

        public void setMaxLength(int maxLength)
        The maximum number of characters that are read or written to/from the cell. Input and output value will be silently truncated to this length. If you want to get an error when field is to long, use the format regexp pattern instead.

        Set to a positive value if maxLength should be used.

        Parameters:
        maxLength - the maxLength to set

      • isMaxLength
